    All Classes and Interfaces

    Classes
    Class
    Description
    App
    Main JavaFX application class for the Gang Y0 restaurant management system.
    Employee
    Represents an employee within the system.
    EmployeeDAO
    The EmployeeDAO class provides methods for accessing and modifying employee data stored in the database.
    ExampleUse
     
    Inventory
    Represents an item in the inventory with a name and quantity.
    InventoryDAO
    The InventoryDAO class provides methods to interact with the inventory table in the database.
    InventoryUsageDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) for retrieving inventory usage information from the database.
    Login
    Handles user authentication and login validation against the employees table.
    loginController
    Controller class for the login interface of the Gang Y0 restaurant management system.
    MenuDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) for performing CRUD operations on the menu table.
    MenuItem
    Represents a menu item with a name, price, and category.
    PrimaryController
    Primary controller for the Gang Y0 restaurant management system manager interface.
    ReportDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) for generating various business reports from the database.
    ReportDAO.ZReportData
    Represents structured data for the end-of-day Z-Report summary.
    ReportDAO.ZReportData.EmployeeSignature
    Represents an employee signature section in the Z-Report.
    SecondaryController
    Cashier-facing POS controller.
    testTransactionDAO
    Test class for TransactionDAO.
    Transaction
    Represents a financial transaction within the system.
    TransactionDAO
    Data Access Object (DAO) class for handling database operations related to transactions.
    TransactionItems
    Represents the relationship between a transaction and an item.
